<inglise> Whereas premiums already paid must be recovered if the obligations under the premium system are not met; whereas, however, in certain cases, and in particular if the recipient is temporarily or permanently unable to fulfil these obligations by reason of circumstances beyond his control and which he cannot remedy save at disproportionate cost to himself (6), it appears justified to release him temporarily or permanently from those obligations; whereas, however, the obligations under the premium system should continue to apply where the holding is transferred; (1) OJ No L 131, 26.5.1977, p. 1. (2) OJ No L 134, 22.5.1978, p. 9. (3) OJ No L 150, 18.6.1977, p. 24. (4) OJ No L 93, 7.4.1978, p. 17. (5) OJ No L 7, 10.1.1978, p. 6. (6) ECR 1968, 549 and 1970, 1125. </inglise>
