<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In cases of force majeure occurring after the application has been approved, Member States may provide that the premiums already paid shall not be recoverable even if the obligations under the scheme have not been fulfilled and, if necessary, the non-marketing or reconversion period may be suspended for a specified period and extended accordingly. </inglise>
<eesti> Juhul kui v&auml;&auml;ramatu j&otilde;ud esineb p&auml;rast taotluse heakskiitmist, v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid ette n&auml;ha, et makstud lisatasusid ei n&otilde;uta tagasi isegi siis, kui kavast tulenevad kohustused on t&auml;itmata, ning vajaduse korral v&otilde;ib turustamata j&auml;tmise v&otilde;i &uuml;mberkorraldamise perioodi t&auml;psustatud ajaks peatada ja seda vastavalt pikendada. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Provision for non-recovery of the premium may, in particular, be made in the following cases: </inglise>
<eesti> Lisatasu tagasi n&otilde;udmata j&auml;tmise v&otilde;ib ette n&auml;ha eelk&otilde;ige j&auml;rgmistel juhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) death of the recipient, provided that he farmed his holding himself; </inglise>
<eesti> a) lisatasu saaja surm, tingimusel, et ta ise haldas oma ettev&otilde;tet; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) an extended period of disability such as to prevent the recipient from carrying on his occupation, provided that he farmed his holding himself; </inglise>
<eesti> b) pikk t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse aeg, mis takistab lisatasu saajat oma t&ouml;&ouml;kohustusi t&auml;itmast, tingimusel et ta ise haldas oma ettev&otilde;tet; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) compulsory purchase of a substantial part of the utilized agricultural area of the holding farmed by the recipient, provided that such compulsory purchase was not foreseeable at the date when the application was approved. </inglise>
<eesti> c) lisatasu saaja haritava majapidamise p&otilde;llumajandusk&otilde;lviku olulise osa sundost, tingimusel et taotluse heakskiitmise kuup&auml;eval ei olnud sellist sundostu v&otilde;imalik ette n&auml;ha. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Provision for suspension of the relevant period may, in particular, be made in the following cases: </inglise>
<eesti> Asjakohase perioodi peatamise v&otilde;ib ette n&auml;ha eelk&otilde;ige j&auml;rgmistel juhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) a serious natural disaster substantially affecting the land farmed by the recipient; </inglise>
<eesti> a) t&otilde;sine loodus&otilde;nnetus, mis kahjustab olulisel m&auml;&auml;ral lisatasu saaja haritavat maad; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) accidental destruction of buildings normally used by the recipient for cattle or sheep farming purposes; </inglise>
<eesti> b) nende hoonete juhuslik h&auml;vimine, mida lisatasu saaja kasutas harilikult kariloomade v&otilde;i lammaste pidamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) an outbreak of epizootic disease affecting all or part of the recipient's cattle or sheep herd. </inglise>
<eesti> c) sellise episootilise haiguse vallandumine, mis m&otilde;jutab kogu lisatasu saaja looma- v&otilde;i lambakarja v&otilde;i osa nendest. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The Member States shall inform the Commission of all cases of force majeure accepted as such by them. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teatavad komisjonile k&otilde;ik v&auml;&auml;ramatu j&otilde;u juhud, mida nad sellisteks tunnistavad. </eesti>
